{"tier":3,"question":"What is 'osmotic pressure' effect when salting vegetables?","answer":"Salt draws water out of vegetable cells by osmosis, wilting and concentrating them","choices":["Salt hardens the cell walls of vegetables","Salt draws water out of vegetable cells by osmosis, wilting and concentrating them","Salt destroys enzymes causing browning","Salt raises the boiling point, cooking vegetables faster"]},
