{"tier":3,"question":"What is 'emulsification' achieved by in vinaigrette?","answer":"Mustard or egg yolk provides emulsifying lecithin molecules that surround oil droplets","choices":["Vigorous shaking of oil and vinegar","Mustard or egg yolk provides emulsifying lecithin molecules that surround oil droplets","Using thick balsamic vinegar only","Adding a thickener like cornstarch"]},
