{"tier":3,"question":"What is 'tenderization' of meat by acid?","answer":"Acids denature surface proteins and break down collagen fibers, softening tough cuts","choices":["Acids draw moisture into meat","Acids denature surface proteins and break down collagen fibers, softening tough cuts","Acids speed up cooking time","Acids preserve the color of meat"]},
